me quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud de Wrenbury I was born in 1110, in Kingsley, Cheshire, England. She married Ranulph de Kingsley II.  (1 Child) in 1135, in Cheshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1151, in Kingsley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1110–1151":"1110–1151","1105–1140":"1105–1140","1135–1244":"1135–1244","1105":"1105","1135":"1135","1244":"1244","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1151":"1151","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Kingsley, Cheshire, England":"Kingsley, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1110–1151":"1110–1151","1105–1140":"1105–1140","1135–1244":"1135–1244","1105":"1105","1135":"1135","1244":"1244","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1151":"1151","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Kingsley, Cheshire, England":"Kingsley, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1110–1151":"1110–1151","1105–1140":"1105–1140","1135–1244":"1135–1244","1105":"1105","1135":"1135","1244":"1244","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1151":"1151","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre","Kingsley, Cheshire, England":"Kingsley, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Maud de Wrenbury I est née en 1110, à Kingsley, Cheshire, Angleterre. Elle a épousé Ranulph de Kingsley II.  (1 Child) en 1135, à Cheshire, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée en 1151, à Kingsley, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 41 ans."},"de":{"1110–1151":"1110–1151","1105–1140":"1105–1140","1135–1244":"1135–1244","1105":"1105","1135":"1135","1244":"1244","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1151":"1151","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Kingsley, Cheshire, England":"Kingsley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Maud de Wrenbury I wurde 1110 in Kingsley, Chesh